rComments: Lots and lots of readings, but very interesting course material and thought-provoking class discussions. Be prepared to study hard for the midterm and to stay on top of the heavy reading in order to do well.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Didn't learn a thing in this class. It's all memorization and exam based so if you are a fan of that which some people are, then definitely take it. I did well but still wouldn't recommend because it didn't do anything for me. Multiple choice and short answers were stupid and the TAs are slow and have no idea what they are doing for this class.

He was funny in class and kept it interesting but there was way too much reading. He would assign 2-3 chapters per week that were each like 30 pages long and all of it was important for the exam. Make sure you pay attention to any lists or anything like the difference between 2 things from text and lectures, those are always on the tests.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read', 'Hilarious']

rComments: Probably the worst prof at U of T. The TA's are even worse; huge disparity among them. Some mark way too easy and one TA in particular is literally the devil reincarnate herself. Teaches inaccurate things and his tests are stupidly hard. He says its 50/50 but its all textbook material. The readings all repeat and it's too much work for repetition
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Best prof I have had at UofT. He is hilarious in class and makes the material really interesting. The midterms/exams are hard and are usually only based off lists mentioned in the textbook and lecture.

Assigns a ridiculous amount of readings per week, especially once you get into CRI210. 6 chapters by week 2! Major assignment handed back AT the final exam, and he flies off right after, so good luck trying to contest your mark. Rarely accessible outside of class, and the exams, while fair, are more-so 80% textbook based.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: 14 years past old rate my profs, definitely not his prime hotness however he is really funny. Midterm was really hard, you don't get the big assignment grade back until AFTER the exam which sucks.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: The man is a God amongst pagans, by far the best professor at this campus.

The higher classes that I took with Prof. Wortley were much better than the 200 - level courses with him. Going to lectures and doing the assigned readings in depth is important, but you definitely get the grade you worked for.
His lectures were ok, neither too dry nor too interesting.
Great prof. Really cares about his students. Tests can be very detailed so make sure you know everything, especially the things he mentions in class. Very approachable.
One of the best professor's I've had by far!
Good professor, his tests are by far fair. Study the lecture slides and memorize lists and you'll get a good mark.

good guy, acessible after class and during office hours.  His tests require you to know specific knowledge about theory and the info he puts up on his slides, but he posts them all, and a good understanding of the textbook bill help you get a good mark.

Wortley grades  tough, but it's all memorization+ he always lists things in lectures so its very straightforward. Lectures are very well organized and he is hilarious and sarcastic and swears sometimes. I'd take all the classes he offers. Even though its a tough A, but attainable B. I think the papers+ assignments are the hardest. Great prof.

Wortley as an individual is great - funny, charming, seems easy to talk to. Wortley as a prof? Not very helpful, doesn't seem to care much about students' performances or even grading papers/tests for that matter. His lectures are easy but tests and assignments disproportionally difficult in comparison.

Took in Fall 2015. Wortley is always very engaging & funny in lecture. However, it's essential to take notes on the textbook - as it is used every week and for tests. His tests, projects, and exams are very tough, but they take into account all the subject matter we discuss in class. The Wortropolis Assignment is tough, but helped with theories.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Paying attention in lecture is key, but you also need to have an idea of whats going on in the textbook. He assigns a lot of material per class, but its not always 100% necessary untill the test comes.

Wortley is a great prof! He is funny and likes to tell stories that relate to the topic.  Some of the topics are dry (theory based), but the assignment is straightforward.  Tests can be tricky (very long), but same for all of his classes.

Professor Wortley is hands down my favourite professor. Really clarifies the material from the readings and has very clear and precise lectures. Favourite part is he is hilarious, really knows how to make a class laugh and keep us interested in the lecture.

Scot Wortley is a great professor. His lectures are clear and he is a very funny and lovable guy. I went to him during his office hours once and he offered help and guidelines on how I could improve on his tests.  If you are good at memorizing lists, then this course will be perfect for you.  I would definitely take one of his classes again!

Professor Wortley is very likeable. He makes you want to engage in his classes- and quite frankly has made me interested in being a criminologist. The amount of reading though- way overboard for just one class. If you are smart about it though, you can weed out the info that you need. Overall, would definitely take any class that he is teaching.

Prof Wortley is a very clear and concise lecturer. He knows what he wants from his students and lets them know what he's looking for. His tests are not hard if you are good at memorizing lists and terms and put effort into all the readings. His lecture slides are crucial for his short answer questions.
The lectures were okayish, neither to dry nor to interesting ( as with all theory courses). Exams weren't hard. If you spend some time studying, you should be good. Overall, I recommend this course
He is a very funny prof, and he always cracked jokes which made the class enjoyable. You need to keep on top of the readings and study ALOT to do well. Overall really loved the course.
awesome prof, usually repeats what's on the slides though. however, on occasion he adds more in lecture. very funny, interesting examples. definitely recommend to anyone!
Good tests. Only problem is he makes us read the textbook and does not always reinforce the material in lecture but tests us on it.

His classes are boring and unengaging, probably because most of the time he simplifies the textbook material to its bare minimum. He can be funny, but otherwise his lectures lack confidence (which is surprising if he's been teaching for so many years now). His test was too narrow in focus; the assignment decent but the TAs mark harshly.

He is a very bright guy. I was very surprised for his first test where most people did horrible because he tests in a way where you need to memorize details and list things. After that you get used to his style and can get easy marks like A to A+. He teaches very well and I enjoyed him as a professor. Would definitely take his class again.
Test and exam are straight forward, just review the slides and textbook (few tricky questions). Expectation of the essay assignment wasn't clear at all.

Very good Professor. He is very clear and exams are very predictable if you study the slides you fail if you study all the material you pass with a B, so it is up to you what you want. He explains the topic very clear with examples and details. His TAs are not very helpful but seriously if you attend the lectures you do not need extra help.

He was a great prof. Very easy to understood and took the time to help students who wanted help. He wasn't going to carry anyone, but definitely went the mile for those who wanted to help themselves. Would find time out of class to meet and help too
Seems like a lazy teacher, he reads slides and doesn't engage with the material, then tests on little nit picked bits of the text.

I've always liked Wortley because his lecture style is very clear and he is very straight forward. Those of you who didn't like him in WDW200 should take his 300 level courses (nobody does well in wdw200 anyway that's just how the course is built). His tests are heavily textbook based which makes him predictable-and easy if you study.

Pretty good teacher. Clear most of the time. Expect tests to be largely based on the textbook which means do your readings! Tests are also largely fair-although there are the one or two odd questions which are pretty difficult to answer. He's a pretty funny guy too-although I do not understand how he is 'hot...' probably because I am a male :/.

He's an excellent lecturer but a pretty lousy person. Extremely unapproachable. It's a good thing that he teaches such a big class, because he wouldn't be able to handle having to interact with students regularly.
Tests are really hard. Boring Lectures. Dissapointing overall.
Amazing prof... extremly funny:D

Lectures were super dry, he loves useless numbers. His tests fluctuate in fairness I went from 63 on the first test to a 96 on the second one. clearly there was no consistency, EVIL TA who seems to be attached to him.
The tests were great for me - the short answer format was really different from what most people are used to. Some people bombed them. It's a required course, and he made the lectures interesting.

really interesting course... ta's... at least mine... didnt know what she was doing...  but the prof is really goood and compared to a whole bunch of tests from psy, these ones are soooo fair
Yes the course is hard, but I'm taking Intro Psych and its brutal too. They have to do that to ween out the weaklings.

This class is easy. THere are a lot of readings but the tests are fair. Guest speakers are interesting. I don't know about the hottness though... maybe 10 years ago.
